http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/%E2%80%98Fundamentalism-posing-threat-to-women%E2%80%99/article14015716.ece

Democratic forces have to unite in the country and across the world to achieve gender equality and fight against discrimination.Speaking at the seminar on International Solidarity for Equality, Justice and Peace on third day of the 20{+t}{+h}National Congress of the National Federation of Indian Women at Ukkunagaram here on Friday, General Secretary Communist Party of India Suravaram Sudhakar Reddy noted that the increasing fundamentalism was posing a threat to women in the country.The increasing focus on Manu Dharma in the name of tradition in the country was encouraging gender discrimination and the obscurantist forces were trying to blame the women for the violence against them. Women have to unite to strive for peace and equality and proper implementation of laws, he said.European nations were facing crisis due to the heavy influx of refugees from countries like Syria. Among the refugees the children and women were the worst sufferers, Mr Sudhakar Reddy noted. President of the Congress Aruna Roy presided over and fraternal delegate from the USA Vinnie Burrows, among others spoke.